description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and clinically experienced Nurse Lead/Operational Manager for the Cardiff Health Access Practice (CHAP)/Alternative Treatment Service (ATS. Safe Haven), based in Cardiff Royal infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CHAP service is the only service in Wales that provides Public Health Screening, health assessments and essential healthcare to newly arrived individuals who are seeking asylum in the UK. The ATS provides general medical services to individuals who cannot access regular GP practice care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following a major review and redesign we now want to appoint to the critical post of Nurse Lead/Operational Manager. The post will be responsible for managing and providing clinical leadership to the department and the MDT on a day to day basis. The person will work closely with the Clinical Director for CHAP and be supported by the Administration and Service Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given the unique nature of this service, we are looking for an individual who has extensive clinical skills and an ability to operationally manage an MDT. Most importantly, we would like someone who has a passion and genuine interest in meeting the complex and wide ranging needs of the people who use the service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
